replyContent: You have the full version, which means you can already adjust the map size. When you press the button 'New game', you'll see a button named 'Customize settings' at the bottom. When you press this button, you can adjust the width and height of the map for new games.

content: Great game. Would add one feature. Ability to port the saved game from the free version onto the full version. I had almost all of the upgrades before I decided to buy the full game. Now I have to start over.
replyContent: Unfortunatly that's impossible to integrate. Android apps are treated as separated containers, which cannot communicate with eachother. And if we use in-app-purchases, you have to be online every time you start the game. However, if your phone is rooted, you can just copy the .json files located in /data/data/nl.palatamedia.minerfree.

replyContent: No, that's because Android treats it as two separate games. And all games have their own storage space, so there is no way to interact, except for when you're using a server. And since for this game a server is useless, and only slows it down, we chose not to use a server. So you see, there's nothing we can do about it.

replyContent: You should try the cooler and the teleporter.

content: I love the game. Very nice original game. I can play this for hours on end. Never had a problem so far. Hope it stays this way. Thanks game creators

Samsung Gallery Note 8.0 Not happy with this game at all. I bought it and now wish I hadn't. If they fix these problem it would be a rocking games like it was for the PC. First off their is not enough ore in the upper levels to fill the gas tank much less to by any extras. I have went almost halfway across the whole mining area without seeing one ore deposit. When you do find some its not enough to fill the gas tank. Yes I know the ore does not fill the gas tank but the money that you receive for it does. And why can't you choose how much gas you want to get. If you don't have enough money to fill the tank it will not allow you to purchase any fuel. Why did you bother putting a alarm for low fuel. If you leave as soon as you hear the alarm you still run out of fuel before you get to the surface. So what good is your alarm, I'll tell you it's worthless. It should give you enough time to pick up one or two pieces of ore right beside you and still make it to the surface when it goes off.  Also the alarm for the low fuel and the full ore alarm are the same. Need to change that. I have a lot more ideas but they limit your criticism or ideas to help. Will update when or if I'm able.
replyContent: We love to hear good ideas, so maybe you could send us an email, and we can sort things out.

content: Seems to be a battery drain playing it. 15 mins playing and I easily drain 20% of my battery life.  I don't know if others have reported this. Other than this, I love this game.  Update: Thanks for the swift response devs. I'd like to blame my battery but my phone is brand new. I've been playing it in airplane mode and the battery drain isn't as bad.
replyContent:
We noticed that too, only not in such extreme forms. At this point, we have no idea why the game uses so much power, and if we're able to cut it down.
If it is possible to solve it, it will be in one of the next updates.

content: Made it quite a ways down now the teleporter only refuels but will not allow teleport back to the surface.
replyContent: Yes, we are aware of that problem, and it is solved in the next update.

content: Needs more upgrades and depth
Great game but the teleporter doesnt take you back to surface it just repairs...
Nice game. But the rewards for clearing percentages of the map are broken.

What kind of crap is this I buy the game and have to start all over again thats bs  Edit I appreciate your quick reply and I'm over it now it would be nice if it were like some apps that are offline where the paid version isn't a new app but an unlock key that unlocks the full game content.
replyContent: No, that's common for most offline apps. Android treats the free and the paid versions as apps that are independent from each other. There is no connection with a server, so everything is stored on your phone, and every app has its own secluded space. That's the way Android works, for example for safety reasons.

content: Similar to one of my other favorite games for the computer (anybody who's played it knows). It's a shame a different developer had to take the mantel to bring said game to Android devices, but it's a solid clone that is one of the best "miner" type games for the OS. Now if only the developer hadn't made the game hack-proof, I'd be well on my way to the bottom! Only gripe is the extreme price raise in items. Overall, 5/5.
Crap
Updates made this a mega keeper. Thanx Dev. (Quick response from devs!!  Awesome game.
replyContent:
We noticed that problem too. With the next update, coming in few days, that should be resolved.
However, if you use the teleporter, it stays where you put it, and you can use it over and over again. The line that says 'single use' shouldn't be there.

content: Upgrades too expensive and the tiers are too extreme. Would also really like to see the option to steer by touching the sides of the screen, instead of tiny buttons in the middle. Ergonomically this is a poor interface.
replyContent: We are currently working on an update. An adjustable interface is one of the changes, which makes it easier to control on a tablet.

content: I play using a tablet and having to use my index finger to steer gets tiring quickly. I'd suggest adding the option to switch the positions of either gauges with the arrows to allow control with the thumbs. ( for either lefties or righties ) [Edit] awesome! Can't wait for the update! Maybe also throw a suggested depth to each cooling upgrade? Might be helpful when upgrading.
replyContent: That's a good suggestion. We'll add an option to change the controls in the next version.
